OL,3,CMeet the tram driver celebrating 50
OL,4,Cyears at the Douglas Horse Tramway
OL,6,FHe then worked his way up to becoming
OL,7,Fa driver in the space of a year, and
OL,8,Fhas spent the last five decades
OL,9,Fdedicated to driving the trams.
OL,11,FWhen asked what has kept Peter working
OL,12,Fat the tramway, he said: "Certainly
OL,13,Fnot the money!".
OL,15,F"People say do you get bored looking
OL,16,Fat the horse's bum all the time - well
OL,17,Fnot really - years gone by there's
OL,18,Fplenty going on on the promenade to
OL,19,Fkeep you alert and keep you watching
OL,20,Fwhat's going on."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
